HMS: Home Management System

--Use Case
The home management system controls all IoT devices at the user's home.

--Triggers
1.A voice/terminal/gesture command to perform an action
2.Timed events
3.External triggers

--Actors
1.The home owner
2.devices
3.network
4.hms

--preconditions
1.IoT devices
2.network

--Goals
schedule and perform tasks automatically

--Not Available
Extension system (modules/plugins)

--Steps of execution
1.The home owner gives a command to hms
2.HMS detects the command and interprets the command
3.HMS performs the command on the objects and sends it over the network
4.the device receives the command and performs the action
5.HMS confirms status of completion for action

